        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 10:53PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1052 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gruver, or 9 miles west of Spearman, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gruver.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
